sql:
SELECT r.CustomerId
FROM receipts r
JOIN items i ON r.ReceiptNumber = i.Receipt
JOIN goods g ON i.Item = g.Id
GROUP BY r.CustomerId, g.Id
HAVING AVG(g.Price) > 5;
question: Find the ids of customers whose average spending for each good is above 5.

sql:
SELECT CustomerId
FROM (
    SELECT r.CustomerId, i.Item, AVG(g.Price) AS avg_spending
    FROM receipts r
    JOIN items i ON r.ReceiptNumber = i.Receipt
    JOIN goods g ON i.Item = g.Id
    GROUP BY r.CustomerId, i.Item
) t
GROUP BY CustomerId
HAVING MIN(avg_spending) > 5;

sql:
SELECT c.Id
FROM customers c
JOIN receipts r ON c.Id = r.CustomerId
JOIN items i ON r.ReceiptNumber = i.Receipt
JOIN goods g ON i.Item = g.Id
GROUP BY c.Id, g.Id
HAVING AVG(g.Price) > 5
INTERSECT

FROM customers c
JOIN receipts r ON c.Id = r.CustomerId

JOIN goods g ON i.Item = g.Id
GROUP BY c.Id
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT g.Id) = (
